<br>
I'm curious, mages, why you use the type of pet you are using.  I've seen the earth pet, fire, and I think air?  What are the reasons you pull up one versus another?<br>
<br>
Others, I often hear complaints about some of the mage pets.  In particular, some say the earth pet shouldn't be allowed because they root.  The air pet does a knockback.  Etc.  Etc.  What are your specific issues with the use of mage pets.<br>
<br>
I know it's extrememly important to keep pets under control at all times.  Any comments on pet control in Fear?  (Heh Heh keep it objective...) <p>Selilya Withertouch<BR>
Winnower of the Violent Harvest <BR>
Devoted Daughter of Innoruuk <BR>
<BR>
<center><img src="http://members.aol.com/selilya/selilya.jpg"  border=0> </center></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uselilya.showPublicProfile?language=EN>selilya</A> at: 5/29/01 11:09:03 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uthorondar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Thorondar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tunare's Fury</span><br>  Posts: 562<br> <font color=#CC9900>(5/29/01 12:02:30 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.watchers-brell.com/images/thor-shirt.jpg height=177 width=162></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Mage Pets on Fear Raids</span><hr size=1> Air - Damage dealing, lowish hps and casts a stun.  Ideal for xp for damage mitigation to tanks, on raids if the mob is stunnable and is being debuffed, this can also help damage mitigation.<br>
<br>
Earth - Best hps available to all mage pets, good damage output and casts a root spell (no damage from root either).  Good for crowd control and good for keeping a mob rooted (rooted mobs can't summon) and allows casters to nuke without fear of repercussions.<br>
<br>
Fire - Least amount of hps, casts a fire dd and has an innate damage shield rumored to be equal to the level of the pet.  Pet is lvl 25, damage shield is 25, etc.  Good for mobs with a fire AE, good for cleaning out greenies, not a great raid mob unless against ae mobs.<br>
<br>
Water - 2nd to most hps, good damage dealer and casts offensive ice based nuke.  Just a good all around damagedealer/fighter/tank pet.  However, no root, no stuns.<br>
<br>
Mages have a variety of reasons for why they would summon different pets, also at 51+, mage pets have different classes they are based upon, ie, water pets are rogues, earth pets are warriors, fire pets are wizzies, air pets are monks.  If you're in a fear-snare group, you'll want the 54 water pet at least to backstab.<br>
<br>
