</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uredspinebladeslinge.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Redspine Bladeslinge</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_ball.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Guardian of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 1012<br> <font color=#CC9900>(5/30/01 3:21:58 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.yellowspine.com/images/jackalope.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Mage Pets on Fear Raids</span><hr size=1> Usually like air pets on Fear for the stunning.  Majority of mobs in can be stunned here and helps reduce dmg from the mob and interupt casting.  Not to mention 50+ mage pets are just plan beasts and can dish out a good deal of damage during a raid.<br>
<br>
I don't allow pets in Hate unless fighting Meastro or other uber mobs.  Pathing in Hate is to muffed up.  You back a mob up against the wall and the pets take off to run around to the opposite side of the wall to attack the mob.  Plus other pathing issues.<br>
<br>
