<br>
HATE:  Watch it on the first level or at least until you start clearing things up ... because pathing sucks.  So for the most part many magi's don't use them on the first level unless things get going rough and they may cast it for a battle then kill it off.  ( it only costs 200-300m ) at 49+ it is quading in the 50+ so that's cheap dmg.   In the 2nd floor once you become situation pathing gets a little better so I understand, and many magi's will bring them up there.<br>
<br>
FEAR:  Not to bad, but you gotta watch it.  High up on the wall it can do funny things, but other than that once your group is in Fear and situated most will pull them up without a problem, then kill them off when you move.   Pet management when moving though has become much easier now that we can summon our pet from a distance with the new pet summon spell.<br>
<br>
<br>
AIR:  Don't here much compliants here, although I think only the magi air pet will work here and it looks pretty different and cool in PoA.  <br>
<br>
Anyway haven't been to either but most of the magi's guides and other folks I have talked to thus far seem to have the above consenus.  However hate seems to be the most troublesome zone to have a pet up in. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uickhorvonmemnoch.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ickhor Von Memnoch</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Gnomosexual</span><br>  Posts: 453<br> <font color=#CC9900>(5/31/01 3:18:05 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Mage Pets on Fear Raids</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Pathing in Hate is to muffed up. You back a mob up against the wall and the pets take off to run around to the opposite side of the wall to attack the mob.<br>
